GUI will require a change in associated robotics as well.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Mixed approach</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is what is usually found in most integrations. It has been found in the real world that any one approach is not sufficient to address all the functional needs of a business ERP system.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But even a custom approach is not without certain limitations. They are discussed below:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Data quality</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Compensation events need to be designed to mitigate transaction failure or to adjust against the adverse business impact of time-consuming ones.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Extra effort has to be put in to create the flexibility of data structures. </li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Backup and Archival necessity</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A contingency plan for backup, backup monitoring, and disaster recovery is vital. This becomes especially complex as cloud services and cloud integration has phased out conventional physical infrastructure. They have their own separate legal regulations that have to be looked into. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Quality Control</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The field and scope of failures and errors in SAP environment and activity is vast. To add to that, a shared test environment isn’t easy to achieve due to the involvement of numerous legacy and SAP systems. Working with multiple languages and protocols is not easy. The challenges in monitoring evolving connections with SAP sub-systems, coupling and decoupling services, time-triggers, particular events that drive certain processes, asynchronous communication in connectors, etc is considerable.&nbsp;<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A significant amount of effort, time and resources are expended by businesses to meet these challenges. Also, this isn\'t something that can be limited to a small or focus group; numerous stakeholders, decision-makers and vendors have to participate.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1>Conclusion</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A well-designed, rigorously checked and diligently monitored SAP integration helps a business reap insights and gain efficiencies. These are must-haves in these times to conquer higher and more complex ground.&nbsp;<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>eFrog’s secure and reliable <a href=\"http://www.efrog.com.au/\">software development solutions</a> help run business processes and conveniently exchange data between onsite infrastructure, cloud platforms, and external third-party applications. The integrations and connectors eFrog provides are easy to learn and assimilate, ensuring that clients don\'t have to waste effort, time or resources on training and staffing around these technologies. The integration designs are created to minimize developmental costs to the client.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '5 Challenges to SAP Integration You Should Know', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '79-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-11-05 05:23:23', '2019-11-05 05:23:23', '', 79, 'http://www.efrog.com.au/blog/2019/11/05/79-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
