(85, 1, '2019-11-08 08:05:15', '2019-11-08 08:05:15', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Why Instagram?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Social media is unquestionably an essential investment in marketing a brand. Instagram has steadily risen through the ranks to dominate all social media platforms for B2C marketers. It is highly rewarding to market on Instagram as it is mobile-based and thus enjoys recognition as one of the platforms with the <a href=\"https://business.instagram.com/?locale=en_AU\">highest user engagement</a>.&nbsp;<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Instagram isn’t just viable for the B2C model but offers a TON of value to B2B models too. It is one of the top platforms for brand promotion and awareness. Instagram features like Stories, linking a website to the profile section or sharing User Generated Content help to connect and engage with other businesses.&nbsp;<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The best way to harness Instagram’s power is by getting in the thick of things - use the 15 tips below to increase your social selling success!<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Create a Business Account </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One normally uses a personal account on any social platform as a way of sharing aspects of his life with his friends and family. But a Business account is run with a very different objective in mind. A business runs its Instagram account to reach and grow an audience base and try to convert them into end-users of its products or services. This is more of a facility to prospect for customers, rather than share personal or private non-professional subject matter. Several businesses, however, choose deliberately to run personal accounts, and this is entirely up to the vision and philosophy of the business owners and decision-makers. But remember your reaction to a very personal and private post of any specific individual on a business page you happened to visit in the past. <br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":91} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://www.efrog.com.au/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Efrog-Blog-Post.jpg\" alt=\"15 Instagram Marketing Tips For Your Brand\" class=\"wp-image-91\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Business profiles have the gist of extensive analytics data that can easily be obtained by the addition of important contact information to the “Bio.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Maintain consistency of Profile Name and Picture </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Consistency of any profile imagery is vital across your social media platforms. Consistency helps to build and maintain brand reputation. Try to use the same profile picture everywhere! This will take some work as you would probably need a lot of time and work to figure out what works with both you and your target audience and what doesn’t. But once you do find “your look,” stick with it. Any Instagrammer will look at the profile photo first, and consciously or unconsciously form impressions. If they continually encounter the same image across all social media platforms, they’ll have an easier time remembering your brand with the content they happen to be consuming at that point in time. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Create an attractive and arresting Profile </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Most likely your services involve myriad workflows and creating value across multiple channels for your consumers. However, resist the temptation to cram in every detail into the “Bio” field. LESS IS MORE. So reserve this critical space for information on item launches, product and service promotions, and marketing drives.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now is the time to talk about one of the most powerful features of Instagram - the clickable link. Please, take the initiative of updating it as frequently as required. There are many more innovative uses for this link than just linking it to the brand website. Why not use the link to help users teleport digitally to content and app download sources? Or whisking your customers away to purchase your products without having to perform lengthy searches or navigation? Or take them where they can quick-register for events? Sounds good?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Repurpose old Content with a Purpose! </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> This is an efficient and tactical marketing move if there ever was one! Don’t let your existing blog posts, ebooks, videos, and webinars become redundant without extracting every possible bit of value from them. Repurpose bits and purposes of all this old content to create newer and appealing content your target audience will happily consume! Did you know that you can make an existing picture appear as new content just by snipping off a relevant portion after zooming in on it? </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Focus on revealing “Behind-The-Scenes” <br></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As consumers, all human beings are very curious about the production process and assembly of the products they find interesting. Everyone has a natural need to know where his or her product came from!<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reveal this. It makes for captivating and gripping content.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Do not get disheartened if you are a service-oriented business and don’t have a physical or tangible product. We still want to see the challenges you face and the routine you adopt to deliver your service. This know-how is part of your brand value and encourages the world to invest more in your brand.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Use strong and high-quality pictures </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":93} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://www.efrog.com.au/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Efrog-Blog-Post-002.jpg\" alt=\"15 Instagram Marketing Tips For Your Brand -002\" class=\"wp-image-93\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> If you’re satisfied with a stock image on your Instagram profile, then you need to redefine your definitions of “attraction” and “marketing.” Whatever your working space looks and feels like, your company’s Instagram image should flawlessly represent your company’s identity and effortlessly broadcast what it stands for. The idea is that Instagram should represent your organization as a vibrant and happening brand. Anything is better than a bland, uninteresting and boring stock image. The idea is to arrest eyeballs, capture interest and provoke thoughts through an image that speaks, rather than place a drab and uninviting visual as your online identity on this platform. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Use the Stories feature </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":94} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://www.efrog.com.au/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Efrog-Blog-Post-003.jpg\" alt=\"15 Instagram Marketing Tips For Your Brand-003\" class=\"wp-image-94\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Build continuous and long-lasting market impression with Stories and Videos. Instagram throws open the doors of business space to the world to give a rare peek into the inner philosophy or “mantra” of a company. Trust us, everyone is tired of the routine ads with stock footage and larger-than-life, unrealistic and unrelatable shots associated with pushy, in-your-face advertising. Use videos and the storytelling facility on Insta to give your business a rare opportunity -&nbsp; to appear human and relatable instead of staying a faceless brand with no personality or social connections.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you need inspiration with this approach we’re discussing, see if this helps - incorporate&nbsp;visuals that clearly show the entire product lifecycle of your brand. Show the material used to make the product and your distribution system. Other approaches include showcasing sketches, blackboard schematics, blueprints or flow charts.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Dabble in User Generated Content (UGC) <br></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is the essence of this platform. UGC is a time-tested marketing treasure.&nbsp;<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Human beings crave recognition. Just think how gratifying it is to have an individual or an organization recognize you publicly for your achievements!&nbsp; Quick replies for comments and direct messages/Ask for honest reviews/Increase engagement and visits to the website. Engage with your audience on an unprecedented level by sharing their content. Appreciate and tag the creators of the UGC and build all-round goodwill for your own brand, like never before. This is a handy approach for repurposing any old content that performed well for your brand on some other social media platform.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The tried and tested hashtag campaign is very effective for bringing people together. You can use it for helping your business clients and followers to come together, create and share UGC and all-round value.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Leverage the power of Trending Hashtags <br></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":96} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://www.efrog.com.au/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Efrog-Blog-Post-004.jpg\" alt=\"15 Instagram Marketing Tips For Your Brand-004\" class=\"wp-image-96\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hashtags have been found to be unmistakably the best way to increase the visibility and reach of a brand. They are perfect for converting followers to and from your clients\' other social media platforms like Facebook and Linked In. You’ll love the resulting level of visibility and engagement!<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hashtags make your posts more easily accessible to users. It is easier to search or organize posts on the basis of topic and context. It is an effective tool for tracking the performance of promotions. Known also as labeling, they allow you to organically attract the interest of thought leaders or influencers in your field.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Use a Friendly, Conversational and Balanced Tone (in every Insta activity) <br></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Please don’t go overboard with the humor!<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It’s mandatory to reflect on whether funny and quirky is right for your brand and your target audience. The tone you adopt in all your communications on your Instagram should be based on how your prospective and existing customers expect to be spoken to. If you focus on “funny” and “friendly” all the time, your customers just may get rubbed off the wrong way and find you patronizing!&nbsp;<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In general, we all&nbsp;prefer a voice that is direct and not too chatty. We want to show that as a brand we are accessible but still interested in professionalism and being business-like. But this direct voice must not be mistaken for being pally or as just downright casual.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Create Clear Calls-To-Action <br></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The idea here is to GENERATE leads. To CONVERT. To CREATE sales. The idea isn’t about a hard sell. Let’s allow this to sink in for a moment.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here’s a simple analogy to understand this. Have you ever tried force-feeding a yelling toddler or a fidgety pet? It just doesn’t work that way, right? Well, it’s the same here.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You may have a fun, well-liked and really enjoyable Instagram page, but unless it helps you gain business, it isn’t much of a profitable venture. Yes, the Instagram profile is intended to show off your brand’s valuable product or service. But don’t get it to turn off a potential consumer with in-your-face advertising.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The trick here is to GUIDE the visitor or follower by providing a clear, unambiguous and polite call-to-action. Tastefully place links in your content they can click on to learn more or purchase your product. It is the link\'s job to take them to a landing page designed to sell. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Use Instagram to complement existing social media platforms <br></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> If you have profitable facebook ads, consider using Instagram as an extension to your existing Facebook ad campaign. Click <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/business/help/1513393428972189?id=1997185213680277\">here</a> for detailed instructions on how to do this. This helps you to take your brand across different age-groups and platforms. Not to mention this is highly cost-effective. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Offer discounts and exclusive offers <br></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":97} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://www.efrog.com.au/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Efrog-Blog-Post-005.jpg\" alt=\"15 Instagram Marketing Tips For Your Brand-005\" class=\"wp-image-97\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to digital marketing guru Neil Patel, “<a href=\"https://neilpatel.com/blog/drive-sales-with-instagram/\">Instagrammers are shoppers</a>.” He recommends making exclusive announcements of your brand’s latest product and sales-drives to your followers. Let them feel special like the early-birds who are proud to jump on a trend before anyone else.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Customers are able to plan ahead and stay ready for their big purchases when they have the discount and offer updates beforehand from Instagram. So go ahead, don\'t shy away from showing your love! Put up announcements, offer extras and treats and then watch your entire stock get sold out within seconds.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Hyper-Target with Paid Ads <br></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Instagram is used by more than a billion humans every month. When it comes to engagement, Instagram has clearly surpassed both Facebook and Twitter.<br>So why not consider Instagram advertising, if your business is seeking to invest in targeting specific interest-based segments of the market? <a href=\"https://blog.hootsuite.com/instagram-ads-guide/#cost\">This article</a> is a treasure-trove of information on the ad formats available on this platform and their associated costs and benefits. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Tap into the goldmine of Influencer Marketing </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a brand, you need to learn to collaborate with influencers. They can promote your products and services and mascot your campaigns like no other! This is nothing new and has been happening for quite some time in the form of celebrity endorsements.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There has been an interesting development in the digital world. Today, content creators with niche audiences are offering more value to brands on any platform of their choosing, but particularly on visually-focused mediums like YouTube and Instagram. Influencers have dedicated and engaged groups of followers. Influencers unlock their loyal fan-following to your brand for a very reasonable price - sometimes it is as economical as providing them with freebies or a complimentary service! And they get so happy that they give you priceless visibility and credibility!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3> Closing Words </h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is no shortcut to Instagram\'s success. There\'s no crack, cheat code or easter egg here. Your Instagram success story will take planning, consistency, and persistence. But take comfort in the fact that our pointers will help&nbsp;guide you stick to the right path.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Not only can Instagram help with brand awareness, but also relatability through the humanization of the brand. A strong content and engagement strategy on Instagram can go a long way in building brand awareness. Instagram is a great way to show the visual side of your brand. A place to showcase your personality with behind the scenes shots!<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We have given you an actionable overview of what you can do to find success on Instagram. But know your purpose on Instagram. If you know your goals, you can formulate your Instagram strategy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Need help creating that perfect brand? <a href=\"http://www.efrog.com.au/\">Let us help tell your brand’s unique story on Instagram today!</a><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '15 Instagram Marketing Tips For Your Brand', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '15-instagram-marketing-tips-for-your-brand', '', '', '2020-03-17 06:16:20', '2020-03-17 06:16:20', '', 0, 'http://www.efrog.com.au/blog/?p=85', 0, 'post', '', 0),
