y specific individual on a business page you happened to visit in the past. <br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Business profiles have the gist of extensive analytics data that can easily be obtained by the addition of important contact information to the “Bio.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Maintain consistency of Profile Name and Picture </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Consistency of any profile imagery is vital across your social media platforms. Consistency helps to build and maintain brand reputation. Try to use the same profile picture everywhere! This will take some work as you would probably need a lot of time and work to figure out what works with both you and your target audience and what doesn’t. But once you do find “your look,” stick with it. Any Instagrammer will look at the profile photo first, and consciously or unconsciously form impressions. If they continually encounter the same image across all social media platforms, they’ll have an easier time remembering your brand with the content they happen to be consuming at that point in time. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> Create an attractive and arresting Profile </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Most likely your services involve myriad workflows and creating value across multiple channels for your consumers. However, resist the temptation to cram in every detail into the “Bio” field. LESS IS MORE. So reserve this critical space for information on item launches, product and service promotions, and marketing drives. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now is the time to talk about one of the most powerful features of Instagram - the clickable link. Please, take the initiative of updating it as frequently as required. There are many more innovative uses for this link than just linking it to the brand website. Why not use the link to help users teleport dig