(129, 1, '2019-11-22 12:46:02', '2019-11-22 12:46:02', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> The right eCommerce website development platform is a must for staying profitable. A real-world, physical storefront is no longer enough to keep a business afloat. Technology has changed this world completely and now all brands are selling their wares online. There is a growing demand for eCommerce website development platforms as more and more brands are establishing themselves online. Building an eCommerce website is no longer difficult, thanks to these amazing development platforms discussed below. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>BigCommerce</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":132} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://www.efrog.com.au/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Best-Ecommerce-Website-Development-Platforn-in-2020-01.jpg\" alt=\"Best-Ecommerce-Website-Development-Platforn-in-2020-01\" class=\"wp-image-132\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>BigCommerce provides both development platforms for shopping carts as well as Saas. It is customizable and flexible since it is built using multiple APIs. It has a store stocked with all kinds of extensions. Its features are almost endless including email marketing, product promotion, automation tools, payment processing options that exclude payment processing fees, etc. The flexibility of the shipping options on this platform deserves special mention. They allow live quotes and rate calculations. It integrates with marketplaces and social networks seamlessly. Along with the ability to sell on multiple channels, it also has a lot of marketing tools with handy URL customization options. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Design customization isn’t very user-friendly. And unlike some platforms, it doesn’t have a built-in POS. There is a sales limit according to the subscription plan. Also, special features like abandoned cart saver are expensive. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Magento</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":134} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://www.efrog.com.au/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Best-Ecommerce-Website-Development-Platforn-in-2020-02.jpg\" alt=\"magento\" class=\"wp-image-134\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Magento is one of the oldest eCommerce website development platforms in the industry and had been holding its own at the top for a very long time. Until it was replaced by Shopify as the marker leader it was widely acknowledged as possibly the best eCommerce website development platform to date. Magento is again, an open-source platform and has the associated benefits of customizability and flexibility. It provides basic analytical tools for optimizing conversion and monitoring web traffic. It is widely preferred in the industry as it supports both MVC and OOP architectures. Customizing and using Magento requires a certain degree of technical skill. A key feature of Magento is that it supports multiple browsers, languages and is compatible with several currencies. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>nopCommerce</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":135} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://www.efrog.com.au/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Best-Ecommerce-Website-Development-Platforn-in-2020-03.jpg\" alt=\"nopCommerce\" class=\"wp-image-135\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is a stable, reliable and highly user-friendly platform due to its high customizability. It is perfect for brands that are seeking an open-source solution that is highly scalable and secure. It features a catalog front-end and an administrative backend for cart building. It is an ASP.NET MVC-based powerful solution that has been downloaded more than 2.5 million times. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The salient features of this platform include ease of drop-shipping and mobile compatibility. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Shopify </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":136} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://www.efrog.com.au/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Buying-Organic-Foods-Online-04.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-136\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shopify is known mostly because it is easy to install. It is a comprehensive solution that comes with a host of options and features. It has gained much popularity due to its vast search volume. There’s no need to acquire any coding knowledge for setting up Shopify as it comes with a wide range of plug-ins and themes. You may use the Shopify POS for setting up an online store and begi9ng selling over this e-commerce platform. It comes with a useful resource called Burst. Shopify Burst is great for getting hold of free stock photos for professional or private use. It also simplifies the receipt of credit card payments.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All that is required to start using Shopify is to sign up with our email address. Building a shop and selling can be started right away. Creating products and optimizing the website content for SEO is really easy The intuitive interface also makes it easy to create products and includes SEO features such as title tags and meta descriptions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Since Shopify uses its own markup language called “Liquid” based on Ruby on Rails, coding changes to the platform on our own is difficult.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>SiteBuilder</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":137} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://www.efrog.com.au/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Best-Ecommerce-Website-Development-Platforn-in-2020-04.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-137\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>SiteBuilder is similar to Wix and is an excellent website builder with dependable but limited eCommerce features. The online shop can be set up only with the highest plan they offer. It has an intuitive drag-and-drop interface like Wix. It comes with everything that a beginner requires – domain, hosting, analytics, SEO, and eCommerce tools. While the number of eCommerce tools is rather small it does offer unlimited bandwidth and storage space. This platform is backed by a good customer support system for people who are new to all this. It has limited templates (around 100)and advanced users will need to look for something else on this list. There is also scope for some advanced features for marketing, payment options and logistics.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Wix</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":138} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://www.efrog.com.au/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Best-Ecommerce-Website-Development-Platforn-in-2020-05.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-138\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Wix is really good for newbies in eCommerce website platform development. No coding is required for setup or customization as there is a simple and easy editor that allows the user to drag and drop content anywhere on the site. In addition to its core website-building functionality, it can easily build an online store. Wix has 500 online-store templates and comes with some stock images. It provides a hopping cart with full functionality. It is a time and cost-saving option as it is a fully-hosted service and works with plenty of apps designed to support it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Since it is primarily a website builder its eCommerce capabilities are limited. Once a website has been published on this platform, the template cannot be changed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>WooCommerce</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":139} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://www.efrog.com.au/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Best-Ecommerce-Website-Development-Platforn-in-2020-06.jpg\" alt=\"WooCommerce\" class=\"wp-image-139\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The base WooCommerce plugin, in addition to many extensions, is free and open-source. It is meant for setting up a store on a WordPress website. A business would need to pay a hosting fee to WordPress. So some technical knowledge is required for setting up this eCommerce website development platform. It comes as a free download and is highly customizable and flexible. It allows the user to pick preferred custom plug-ins, website themes, and payment gateway.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>WooCommerce is user-friendly but obviously lacks dedicated customer service. The interface is clean and modern.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Get Started Now</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>eFrog specializes in identifying the primary needs of your business and then recommending the best-suited eCommerce website development platform. We help you with all your queries so that you can compare and pick the best.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Along with emerging eCommerce development platforms, 2020 is also going to witness the rise of new website design trends. Click <a href=\"http://www.efrog.com.au/blog/2019/11/11/the-top-9-website-designing-trends-shaping-2020/\">here</a> to read all about them and stay updated on what’s happening in the website design industry. Please do not hesitate to <a href=\"http://www.efrog.com.au/#contactForm\">contact us</a> for a free consultation, either for getting help with your eCommerce website design platform or for any other need.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '7 Best eCommerce Website Development Platforms in 2020 and Beyond', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '7-best-ecommerce-website-development-platforms-in-2020-and-beyond', '', '\nhttp://www.efrog.com.au/blog/2019/11/11/the-top-9-website-designing-trends-shaping-2020/', '2020-03-17 06:16:17', '2020-03-17 06:16:17', '', 0, 'http://www.efrog.com.au/blog/?p=129', 0, 'post', '', 0),
